  "local_port": 35280,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I make best Szechuan noodles?",
  "response": "Making the best Szechuan noodles requires a balance of bold, spicy, and flavorful ingredients, as well as proper technique. Here's a step-by-step guide to create authentic and delicious Szechuan noodles:\n\n---\n\n### **Ingredients**  \n#### For the Noodles:\n- 200g fresh wheat noodles or dried egg noodles  \n- 1 tbsp vegetable oil (to prevent sticking)  \n\n#### For the Szechuan Sauce:\n- 2 tbsp Szechuan peppercorns (lightly toasted and ground)  \n- 2 tbsp chili oil (store-bought or homemade)  \n- 1 tbsp soy sauce  \n- 1 tbsp black vinegar (or rice vinegar as a substitute)  \n- 1 tbsp sesame paste or peanut butter  \n- 1 tsp sugar  \n- 1 tsp minced garlic  \n- 1 tsp minced ginger  \n- 1-2 tbsp chili flakes (adjust to spice preference)  \n- 1 tsp salt (adjust to taste)  \n\n#### For the Toppings (optional):\n- Thinly sliced cucumber  \n- Scallions (finely chopped)  \n- Crushed peanuts  \n- Fried shallots  \n- Blanched bok choy or spinach  \n\n---\n\n### **Steps**  \n\n1. **Prepare the Noodles:**  \n   - Cook the noodles according to the package instructions until al dente.  \n   - Drain and rinse under cold water to stop the cooking process. Toss with a bit of vegetable oil to prevent sticking.  \n\n2. **Make the Szechuan Sauce:**  \n   - Toast the Szechuan peppercorns in a dry pan over medium heat until fragrant. Grind them into a fine powder using a mortar and pestle or spice grinder.  \n   - In a mixing bowl, combine the ground Szechuan peppercorns, chili oil, soy sauce, black vinegar, sesame paste, sugar, garlic, ginger, chili flakes, and salt. Mix well until smooth. Adjust the seasoning to your taste.  \n\n3. **Assemble the Dish:**  \n   - Place the cooked noodles in a large bowl.  \n   - Pour the Szechuan sauce over the noodles and toss thoroughly to coat evenly.  \n\n4. **Add Toppings:**  \n   - Garnish with your choice of toppings, such as sliced cucumber, scallions, crushed peanuts, or fried shallots.  \n   - For extra freshness, add blanched greens like bok choy or spinach.  \n\n5. **Serve:**  \n   - Serve immediately, with extra chili oil or Szechuan peppercorns on the side for those who want more heat and tingle.  \n\n---\n\n### **Tips for the Best Szechuan Noodles:**  \n- **Chili Oil:** If making homemade chili oil, infuse dried chili flakes in hot oil for a more robust flavor.  \n- **Szechuan Peppercorns:** These are essential for the signature numbing sensation (ma la).  \n- **Noodles:** Use fresh noodles for a chewier texture, or substitute with ramen or udon noodles if unavailable.  \n- **Adjust Heat:** Customize the spice level by adjusting the amount of chili oil and flakes.  \n\nEnjoy your bold, spicy, and flavorful Szechuan noodles!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
